HEADWORD: dalo
<hw>dalo</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a herb of the Pacific islands
(<spn>Colocasia esculenta</spn>) grown throughout the tropics for its
edible root and in temperate areas as an ornamental for its large glossy
leaves.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> taro, taro plant, dasheen, <spn>Colocasia
esculenta</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
